summary.para: Defines the CommentProperties Class.
This class is available in Office 2010 and above.
When the object is serialized out as xml, it's qualified name is x:commentPr.

remarks.format:
## Remarks [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlnoticeiso.md)]
**commentPr (Comment Properties)**
This element specifies the visual and positional properties of a comment.
[*Example*: In the following example, the comment's visual representation resizes with the
```xml <comment … > <text> … </text> <commentPr autoFill="false"> <anchor moveWithCells="true" sizeWithCells="true"> <from> … </from> <to> … </to> <anchor> </commentPr> </comment> ```
*end example*]
|Parent Elements| |---------------------| |comment (§18.7.3)|
|Child Elements|Subclause| |--------------------|---------------| |anchor (Object Cell Anchor)|§18.3.1.1|
[*Note*: The W3C XML Schema definition of this element’s content model (CT_CommentPr) is located in §A.2. *end note*]
[!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlcopyrightiso.md)]
